      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i was looking through some old nasa mission logs from the late 60s and something isn't adding up. the telemetry data for the apollo missions seems way too clean, almost like it was sanitized. i have a theory that the landing actually revealed something massive—like some kind of structure—and the public narrative was changed to hide it. can you help me look for any gaps or inconsistencies in the archived mission reports that might suggest they were covering something up?",
